Backend & Logic Spec — v1
Project: PRINTR Powerball — a 15-minute on-chain raffle for holders of a Solana token launched on PRINTR.
Audience: Engineering agent. This is the v1 spec — explicitly scoped small. Many "nice-to-haves" are deferred. Where a decision is left to you, it's marked [DECIDE]. Where something must be confirmed against external docs (PRINTR SDK, RPC provider), it's marked [VERIFY].

1. Concept (v1 simplified)
Every 15 minutes, one wallet that holds more than 0.2% of total supply at draw time is selected at random. That wallet receives 100% of the trading fees earned by the token's creator wallet on PRINTR over the round.
v1 simplifications:

Equal odds for everyone eligible. No weighting by holdings, no streak boost. (We'll add weighting in v2.)
No wallet connection on the site — the frontend is read-only.
No database — round history lives in a JSON file on disk; live state lives in memory.

If a wallet drops below 0.2% before the draw, they're simply not in the snapshot when the draw runs.
Everything must still be publicly auditable: random seed source, holder snapshot, winner pick, fee claim transaction, and payout transaction.

